    "body": "yes this happens after we process the 1st block of an epoch where `stateRoot` is always `ZERO_HASH`. I don't remember in which cases we use this state, if yes we should add more comments there\r\n\r\nto add more context, this `{root: blockRoots[n], epoch: e}` and the regular/most used checkpoint state `{root: blockRoots[n-1], epoch: e}` (where `n` is the first slot of epoch `e`) share a lot of common data so this is not a big issue",
