    "body": "> to add more context, this {root: blockRoots[n], epoch: e} and the regular/most used checkpoint state {root: blockRoots[n-1], epoch: e} (where n is the first slot of epoch e) share a lot of common data so this is not a big issue\r\n\r\nIt's an issue yes because if there's a re-org on the begning of the epoch you can no longer use that state because it has already processed the first block. If we want to store a regular state in the cache, that's why the state cache exist. Why duplicate it and store also on checkpoint state where it may be miss-used?",
